{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9edff517-12e0-4785-9d18-b71ba53dcaee","content":"There's no workflow file in the current directory, so I'll give you the general guidance for switching to NuGet trusted publishing (OIDC). Here are the key changes:\n\n### 1. Register your package on nuget.org for trusted publishing\n\n- Go to **nuget.org → Manage Package → Trusted Publishers**\n- Add your GitHub repository (owner, repo, optional branch/environment filters)\n\n### 2. Update your GitHub Actions workflow\n\n**Add `id-token: write` permission:**\n```yaml\npermissions:\n  id-token: write   # Required for OIDC token\n  contents: read\n```\n\n**Replace the API key push step:**\n\nBefore:\n```yaml\n- name: Push to NuGet\n  run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }} --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\nAfter:\n```yaml\n- name: Push to NuGet (trusted publishing)\n  run: dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n  env:\n    NUGET_AUTH_TOKEN: ''  # not needed with trusted publishing\n```\n\nOr more explicitly, use the **`dotnet nuget push`** with the `--api-key` flag replaced by the OIDC flow — the .NET 9+ SDK natively supports this:\n\n```yaml\n- name: Push to NuGet (OIDC)\n  run: |\n    dotnet nuget push **/*.nupkg \\\n      --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json \\\n      --api-key az\n```\n\nThe special `az` key tells the SDK to use the ambient OIDC credential.\n\n### 3. Summary of changes\n\n| Area | Old | New |\n|------|-----|-----|\n| **nuget.org** | API key in secrets | Trusted publisher config |\n| **Permissions** | none needed | `id-token: write` |\n| **Push command** | `--api-key ${{ secrets.NUGET_API_KEY }}` | `--api-key az` (OIDC) |\n| **Secret** | `NUGET_API_KEY` | Can be **removed** |\n\n### 4. Optional but recommended\n\n- Use a **GitHub Environment** (e.g., `nuget-publish`) with protection rules, and scope the trusted publisher to that environment on nuget.org.\n- Ensure you're on **.NET SDK 9.0.200+** which has built-in OIDC support.\n\nIf you share your workflow file, I can make the exact edits for you.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"dc066800-c0fa-49d8-8b60-64a36f81ce0c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The working directory is empty. The user is asking a general question about switching from NuGet API key to trusted publishing (OIDC). Let me provide guidance based on my knowledge.","outputTokens":691,"requestId":"B80A:2F053:D01F03:EE7AA2:69F2A83D"},"id":"34575742-5004-4a88-a1c3-24477ffdb7c0","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:54:38.127Z","parentId":"c8b83db9-69e6-4abe-901c-5e9b4b063131"}
